.TH XPWD 1 "2026-05-15" "User Commands" "CLI-Improved Manual"
.SH NAME
xpwd \- print name of current/working directory (smart-link version)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xpwd
[\fIOPTION\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Print the full filename of the current working directory. 
.PP
This version is a "reduced-friction" wrapper designed to identify symbolic link 
paths. If the logical path (where you think you are) differs from the physical 
path (where the disk says you are), it displays both joined by an arrow.
.SH INSTALLATION
Copy the script from the GitHub repository to your $PATH, typically /usr/local/bin.
.SH NOTES
If no symbolic link is detected, the script transparently executes the 
standard system \fB/bin/pwd\fR.
